                },
                {
                    "attributes" : {
                        "POSITION" : 5,
                        "NORMAL" : 6,
                        "TEXCOORD_0" : 7,
                        "TEXCOORD_1" : 8
                    },
                    "indices" : 4,
                    "material" : 0
                },
                {
                    "attributes" : {
                        "POSITION" : 9,
                        "NORMAL" : 10,
                        "TEXCOORD_0" : 11,
                        "TEXCOORD_1" : 12
                    },
                    "indices" : 13,
                    "material" : 0
                }
            ]
        }
    ],`

for vertices count smaller than 65535:
`  "meshes" : [
        {
            "name" : "East_Van_Showcase_Skytrain_Icing_mesh.000",
            "primitives" : [
                {
                    "attributes" : {
                        "POSITION" : 0,
                        "NORMAL" : 1,
                        "TEXCOORD_0" : 2,
                        "COLOR_0" : 3
                    },
                    "indices" : 4,
                    "material" : 0
                }
            ]
        }
    ],`

One of the short term solution is to separate the mesh to make sure the mesh vertices count under 65535 manually.

Thank you!

AnimatedTriangle has an issue with antipodal quaternions, cf. https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Sample-Models/issues/185 and https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF/issues/1395.

The way I solved this was to

